sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant NotebookRec as Notebook Reconciler
    participant Kubelet as Kubelet<br/>10250/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant NotebookPod as Notebook Pod<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Service as Notebook Service<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant CullingRec as Culling Reconciler
    participant ExtUser as External User

    Note over User,NotebookPod: Flow 1: Notebook Creation
    User->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (JWT)
    K8sAPI-->>NotebookRec: Watch Event<br/>(Internal)
    NotebookRec->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet + Service<br/>+ VirtualService<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI->>Kubelet: Schedule Pod<br/>HTTPS/10250 mTLS
    Kubelet->>NotebookPod: Start Container<br/>(Container runtime)

    Note over CullingRec,NotebookPod: Flow 2: Idle Notebook Culling
    CullingRec->>Service: GET /api/kernels<br/>HTTP/80 (no auth)
    Service->>NotebookPod: Forward Request<br/>HTTP/8888
    NotebookPod-->>Service: Kernel Status
    Service-->>CullingRec: Response
    CullingRec->>Service: GET /api/terminals<br/>HTTP/80
    Service->>NotebookPod: Forward Request<br/>HTTP/8888
    NotebookPod-->>Service: Terminal Status
    Service-->>CullingRec: Response
    CullingRec->>K8sAPI: Delete Idle Notebook<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token

    Note over ExtUser,NotebookPod: Flow 3: Istio VirtualService Routing
    ExtUser->>Gateway: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.3<br/>Auth: None/OAuth2
    Gateway->>Service: HTTP/80<br/>mTLS<br/>Istio Peer Auth
    Service->>NotebookPod: HTTP/8888<br/>mTLS<br/>Istio sidecar
    NotebookPod-->>Service: Response
    Service-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>ExtUser: Response
